  "prompt": "Are there ways to not let depression affect your schoolwork?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help manage depression and maintain academic performance:\n\n1. Seek professional help\n- Talk to a counselor or therapist\n- Consider medication if recommended by a professional\n- Join support groups\n\n2. Create structure and routine\n- Set a consistent study schedule\n- Break tasks into smaller, manageable steps\n- Use planners or digital tools to track assignments\n\n3. Practice self-care\n- Maintain regular sleep schedule\n- Eat healthy meals\n- Exercise regularly\n- Practice stress-reduction techniques like meditation\n\n4. Communicate with professors/teachers\n- Let them know about your struggles\n- Request accommodations if needed\n- Ask for extensions or support\n\n5. Build a support network\n- Talk to friends and family\n- Connect with classmates\n- Don't isolate yourself\n\n6. Use academic resources\n- Study groups\n- Campus tutoring centers\n- Academic advisors\n\n7. Develop coping mechanisms\n- Positive self-talk\n- Mindfulness techniques\n- Journaling\n- Time management skills\n\n8. Be kind to yourself\n- Don't be too hard on yourself\n- Celebrate small achievements\n- Recognize that managing depression is challenging\n\nRemember, everyone's experience is different. Finding the right combination of strategies takes time and patience.",
